channel.title: Holy Crap guys, I'm internet famous now.
channel.description:
I apparently have some kinda stalker that's following me around online and collecting stuff from various youtube and myspace accounts that I haven't used in years.
[url]https://www.theanimereality.com/tag/greyacumen/[/url]
I know it's supposed to be mocking me and stuff, but I don't see how I can take it seriously since I was only goofing around to begin with. Hell, with support, I could become a full fledged meme!
C'mon guys, help make it happen!

item.title: Holy Crap guys, I'm internet famous now.
item.dc:creator: AntiBeast
item.description:
Level:

See, but those are normal pastimes that don’t require you to dress up as Neo and…

Normal is just whatever society deems acceptable. Not a fair argument, if he enjoys sword combat and anime etc and wants to as he says, indulge in such hobbies, then let him.

This is the second time in days someone has posted something in these forums and the community rips him apart relentlessly for no reason at all. After seeing such a community in action i no longer think other gaming communities like GunZFactor are so bad, when i use to buy into all that crap about how terrible everyone is to each other.

As for the OP. I cant support this meme dream. Honestly i find these videos pretty boring with the exception of finding out that i was right, that filming in such location will result in unwanted vehicle drive by’s lol. But keep doing what your doing and i wish you the best with your fiance.

item.title: Holy Crap guys, I'm internet famous now.
item.dc:creator: Grey_Acumen
item.description:
Hey, I think the doofus actually revealed himself today. He had his whole steam page done up to look like me and actually requested a chat where he tried to claim i was impersonating him.
I laughed at him, checked his aliases, then blocked communications from him, and now that he’s changed his page back, he’s still is showing up as being blocked.

Steam Online Conduct:

Defame, abuse, harass, stalk, threaten or otherwise violate the legal rights (such as rights of privacy and publicity) of others.

Restrict or inhibit any other user from using and enjoying Steam services, software or other content.

Create a false identity for the purpose of misleading others.

Wow, three points easy.
